summary: The document is an FBI record related to the JFK assassination, specifically concerning inquiries about John Roselli's whereabouts and federal income tax returns. It includes communications between the FBI's Los Angeles office and the Director, dated November 19, 1962. The document is marked as unclassified and was released with deletions.
key_findings: The document pertains to the JFK assassination investigation.
It focuses on John Roselli, including attempts to locate him and inquiries about his federal income tax returns.
The document was reviewed by the PRAJPK Task Force in November 1962.
It was released with deletions on January 15, 1999, under certain restrictions.
